President Obama issued a statement on Yom HaShoah, Holocaust Remembrance Day, expressing solidarity with people around the world in remembering the six million Jews who died in the Holocaust. He emphasized the importance of not just remembering, but also taking action to prevent future atrocities and standing against ignorance and anti-Semitism. The President also mentioned his upcoming visit to the United States Holocaust Memorial Museum and highlighted the significance of the 100th anniversary of Raoul Wallenberg's birth.